LITTER (De-cluttering)**\nNo words were split into multiple entries. The example provided in the protocol, 'ጨምሯልለሶስተኛ' ➔ 'ጨምሯል', 'ለሶስተኛ', indicates splitting distinct lexical units that are merged. Enclitic particles such as 'ም' (also/and), 'ና' (and), and 'ን' (accusative marker) are considered orthographically attached to their preceding word in Amharic and were therefore not separated into distinct entries for the 'word' field. Their presence is reflected in the comprehensive translation.\n\n**PROTOCOL 2: THE JUDGE (Semantic Filtering)**\nTwo entries were discarded as semantic nonsense: 'ከሙኑም' and 'ከሙኑንም'. These character combinations do not correspond to any recognizable Amharic words or common loanwords, even with minor corrections.\n\n**PROTOCOL 3: THE CORRECTOR (Repair vs. Discard)**\nOne word was corrected: 'ከሙዚቀኝነታተቸው' was identified as a likely OCR error and corrected to 'ከሙዚቀኝነታቸው'. This correction was a 'Scholarly Guess' based on the high probability of a single character duplication ('ተ') and the existence of the morphologically sound word 'ሙዚቀኝነታቸው' (their musicianship). No punctuation stripping was necessary as no attached punctuation was present in the valid words.\n\n**PROTOCOL 4: THE LEMMATIZER (Global Citation Form)**\nFor each valid word, the base dictionary entry (infinitive or root noun) was identified. For example, 'ከመፈጠርዋ' was lemmatized to 'መፍጠር', and 'ከሚሆኑላችሁ' to 'መሆን'.\n\n**PROTOCOL 5: THE TRANSLATOR (Nuance Expansion)**\nComprehensive English synonyms were provided to capture the full meaning of each Amharic word in its given context.\n\n**PROTOCOL 6: THE GRAMMARIAN (Linguistic Tagging)**\nEach word was assigned to one of the eight high-level linguistic categories (Noun, Verb, Adjective, Adverb, Pronoun, Preposition, Conjunction, Interjection). Morphological details were intentionally excluded from the 'pos' field.\n\n**PROTOCOL 7: THE FILTER (Size Constraint)**\nAll remaining words and their roots consist of at least two characters, adhering to the size constraint.\n\n**PROTOCOL 8: EXECUTIVE SUMMARY**\nThis summary reflects on the application of all protocols, detailing specific decisions regarding splitting, discarding, and corrections, including 'Scholarly Guesses' where applicable.","input_words":["ከመፈጠርዋ","ከመፈጥፈጥ","ከመፈፀሟም","ከመፋቁ","ከመፍላት","ከመፍረዳችን","ከመፍቀዳቸው","ከመፍታቷ","ከሙሴቬኒ","ከሙቀትም","ከሙታንስ","ከሙኑም","ከሙኑንም","ከሙዚቀኝነቱ","ከሙዚቀኝነታተቸው","ከሙፍቲህ","ከሚሆኑላችሁ","ከሚሆኑትና","ከሚሆናቸው","ከሚሆንልህ","ከሚሆንበትን","ከሚለምኑ","ከሚለቅሙት","ከሚለኩት","ከሚለዩባቸው","ከሚለያዩን","ከሚለይዋቸው","ከሚለገሱት","ከሚሉአት","ከሚሊኒዬም"],"batch_number":null,"batch_label":null,"model_version":"gemini-2.5-flash"},{"id":"3ce05b30-f5db-4cb5-9bca-f80d1210fbbb","created_at":"2026-03-04T07:47:53.145778+00:00","word":null,"source_file":"rare_words_17/chunk_0481.txt","batch_index":0,"words":[{"pos":"Noun","root":"ሕይወት","word":"በሕወቴ","synonyms":["in my life","during my life"],"importance":8},{"pos":"Verb","root":"መሞት","word":"ሙቼም","synonyms":["even if I die","having died","after my death"],"importance":7},{"pos":"Noun","root":"መታጠብ","word":"ስለመታጠብና","synonyms":["about washing","concerning washing","regarding washing and"],"importance":7},{"pos":"Verb","root":"መሽመድመድ","word":"ሊሽመደመድና","synonyms":["to be crushed and","to be shattered and","to be crumbled and"],"importance":7},{"pos":"Noun","root":"ፊውዳሊዝም","word":"ፊውዳሊዝምን","synonyms":["feudalism"],"importance":9},{"pos":"Adjective","root":"መመንዘር","word":"ያልተመነዘረ","synonyms":["unconverted","unexchanged","uncashed"],"importance":8},{"pos":"Noun","root":"ዜግነት","word":"ስለዜግነቱ","synonyms":["about his citizenship","concerning his citizenship","regarding his citizenship"],"importance":8},{"pos":"Noun","root":"ዘመን","word":"ዘመን","synonyms":["time","era","period","age"],"importance":9},{"pos":"Noun","root":"ቃል","word":"ቃል","synonyms":["word","promise","vow","utterance"],"importance":9},{"pos":"Verb","root":"መወዳደር","word":"ይወዳደሩበት","synonyms":["they compete in it","where they compete","they contend in it"],"importance":7},{"pos":"Noun","root":"ምሁር"